he's only 11 years old!

802
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,740
He's all I have left.

803
00:40:43,807 --> 00:40:45,907
Do you understand that?
Stop it, Mom.

804
00:40:45,973 --> 00:40:49,206
You shouldn't get in trouble
for what I did.

805
00:40:51,140 --> 00:40:53,074
I had to kill them.

806
00:40:53,140 --> 00:40:54,673
They were
holding me back.

807
00:40:54,740 --> 00:40:58,306
They were holding
the whole school back.

808
00:40:58,373 --> 00:41:00,206
The whole school was suffering

809
00:41:00,273 --> 00:41:01,873
because of those
stupid kids.

810
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:03,640
Because of how bad

811
00:41:03,707 --> 00:41:06,040
our overall grades
and test scores were.

812
00:41:06,107 --> 00:41:07,273
Even some
of the teachers

813
00:41:07,339 --> 00:41:08,907
were leaving for other schools.

814
00:41:08,973 --> 00:41:10,800
Somebody had to do something.

815
00:41:11,128 --> 00:41:13,206
Why Sam Tewsbury?

816
00:41:14,540 --> 00:41:16,940
I saw Mr. Tewsbury
in the classroom.

817
00:41:17,007 --> 00:41:19,940
I heard him
question the kids.

818
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:24,573
I was certain he suspected a kid
was behind all the deaths.

819
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:25,425
It was only a matter of time

820
00:41:25,425 --> 00:41:27,273
before he figured
everything out.

821
00:41:27,339 --> 00:41:29,506
He was a smart man.

822
00:41:29,573 --> 00:41:32,239
Almost as smart as me.

823
00:41:32,306 --> 00:41:35,973
So you sent him
Nietzsche's book?

824
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:38,239
My mom's copy, actually.

825
00:41:38,306 --> 00:41:40,040
It's her code
to live by.

826
00:41:40,107 --> 00:41:43,206
"What doesn't kill me
makes me stronger. "

827
00:41:43,273 --> 00:41:46,040
You took quite a risk,
licking the toad venom.

828
00:41:46,107 --> 00:41:47,473
Why?

829
00:41:47,540 --> 00:41:49,174
To blend in with the others.

830
00:41:49,239 --> 00:41:51,675
Throw suspicion off myself.

831
00:41:51,675 --> 00:41:54,473
You drew your own blood,
switched the samples

832
00:41:54,540 --> 00:41:58,107
and you made your mom believe
you were terrified of needles.

833
00:41:58,174 --> 00:42:00,007
I made her believe
a lot of things.

834
00:42:01,540 --> 00:42:03,815
When was it going to end?

835
00:42:03,815 --> 00:42:07,238
When someone was smart enough
to stop me, I guess.

836
00:42:08,007 --> 00:42:09,425
Did you know that
the comic book,

837
00:42:09,425 --> 00:42:12,640
<i>Superman, was actually based
on Nietzsche's philosophy?</i>

838
00:42:13,550 --> 00:42:18,074
"Up, up and away... "

839
00:42:27,873 --> 00:42:30,840
How'd you like to be
the court-appointed psychiatrist

840
00:42:30,907 --> 00:42:32,740
whose full-time job
is observing

841
00:42:32,807 --> 00:42:34,940
little Stephen Brown
for a decade or two?

842
00:42:35,007 --> 00:42:38,707
I can think of worse things
to do for a day.

843
00:42:40,373 --> 00:42:43,074
So, Hood...

844
00:42:43,140 --> 00:42:45,640
what were you like
as an 11-year-old boy?

845
00:42:49,238 --> 00:42:51,675
I was kind of like
Stephen, I guess.

846
00:42:53,107 --> 00:42:55,406
I wanted to compete
with the best.

847
00:42:55,473 --> 00:42:57,925
But it's hard to know
how good you are,

848
00:42:57,925 --> 00:42:59,573
if you kill off the competition.

849
00:43:02,074 --> 00:43:04,540
Well, I for one am relieved

850
00:43:04,606 --> 00:43:07,040
that you used that brain
of yours for good.

851
00:43:07,107 --> 00:43:08,606
Thank you.

852
00:43:08,673 --> 00:43:10,873
Maybe I just
never got caught.

